cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with reducing service delay in a Video on Demand system over a wireless mobile network, which involves network infrastructure and multimedia content delivery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a caching mechanism to improve performance, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the balancing mechanism, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
